                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1595: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-25T13:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1919, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 11.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Junta Central electoral college has declared the assembly, presided over by
                    Pino Guerra, represents the Liberal Party. Doctor Zayas issues a statement
                    calling on his friends and adherents to be calm, saying that he will now appeal
                    to the Supreme Court. He will have other remedies which he is resolved to
                    exercise. This means the separation of the Zayas following from the Liberal
                    Party.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
